text: Write your abstract here. Your thesis abstract presents a concise summary of the thesis (research problem or issue, the methods or approach used, and results).

title: 3  Introduction
text: Write your introduction here. You should present the topic and relevant background information. Detail the research problem and hypothesis and provide an overview of the key points of the paper.

6  Results
text:
Write your results here. Report the findings of your study based upon the information gathered as a result of the methodologies you applied. It should simply state the findings, without bias or interpretation, and arranged in a logical sequence.

6.0.1 Cross Referencing Tables and Figures
Within your results and discussion, you can refer to specific figures and tables from your methogologies such as Figure 5.1.

title: 7  Conclusion
text: Write your conclusion here. Conclusions should summarize the problem, the solution and its main innovative features, outlining future work on the topic or application scenarios of the proposed solution.
